Vele van jullie hebben eigenlijk geen flauw idee wie ik ben, dus wie ben ik nou eigenlijk?

Mijn naam is Moswen, ja echt en ik ben Surinaams, ja echt 🇸🇷. Geboren in Amsterdam zuidoost ❌❌❌ en een 90’s baby 👶🏼. 

Ik ben in 2012 begonnen met fitness omdat ik bij de marechaussee wilde. Tijdens mijn fitness journey maakte ik fitness/motivatie filmpjes en die postte ik op Facebook een jaar later op instagram. Ik motiveerde toen al heel veel mensen om ook te sporten in de sportschool, ook werd ik vaak benaderd om personal training te geven. Ik ben toen op de ouderwetse manier begonnen met het zijn van een PT. Certificaten behalen, STAGE lopen enzo🥴 (ja jongens toen liepen we stage in een sportschool🤣). 

Maar goed meer over 🙋🏾‍♂️.
• Fave food: Nasi & tjauw min🍝
• Ik ben een ochtendmens 😴 
• Ik heb 2 kinderen 👶🏼 , een zoon(10), dochter (3).
• Ik ben 1,84cm lang. Mensen die me nog nooit hebben gezien denken altijd dat ik kort ben 😶.

6 THINGS I WSH I COULD TELL EVERYBODY BEFORE THEY START GETTING IN SHAPE....

Thinking back on when my fitness journey started there are a lot of things that I wish I knew.

I could have avoided feeling burnt out and confused at some points.

Like, back in the day when I used to SLAM down whey protein shakes right before a workout and wonder why I felt so sick of you hours later 😂

I was following what everyone else was doing and It took me a while to figure out that dairy just doesn't work well with me.... and that it takes a while to digest protein.

No one is perfect though and it is definitely better to start sooner than later.

These few pointers worth being reminded of...

1) Be grateful for your all of your progress. Get inspired by others without being envious. Do the work to love your body, as cliche as it sounds. This will help you avoid neglecting yourself into a cycle of giving up and starting all over.

2) You don't need intense workouts to get results. You need to learn to challenge yourself and follow the right strategy.

3) Getting clear on why you want to is the most important piece. Your mindset matters the most.

4) Whole food is the answer. The closer it is to nature, the better. When you eat well you feel better.

5) Getting in shape is 24/7 investment that requires you to listen to your body... but it's okay to clock out and just enjoy yourself from time to time.

6) It's never too late to start or re-start. Just be consistent when you do and you will go very far.

-Coach Des ✌🏾

The site of a battle between 2 giants, a home site of NYC’s Indigenous people, tree traversing, rock climbing and more.

I hike to a spot where according to the local Siwanoy people (A branch of Lenape), a fierce competition between the creator and his twin brother the destroyer is believed to have taken place. 

It is said that this took place in an effort to win there mother’s favor, and the right to oversee the matters on the earth. 

On this occasion the creator gained the upper hand and his brother retreated, hurling boulders back at his brother as he escaped. These boulders landed all over the area I visited and are here to this day.

The 2021 NFL draft came and went without a single player from a historically Black college or university (HBCU) being selected. Jackson State University coach and NFL Hall of Famer Deion Sanders vented his frustrations, sending a message on Instagram saying players from HBCU programs were “NEGLECTED AND REJECTED.”

While this 2021 class wasn’t the best year for HBCU athletes, there’s hope the number of recruits increases in the coming years. Next season the program will host an All-Star game to give teams the opportunity to see roughly 100 prospects.

今夜は脚が重かったぁ🥲しかも、ふくらはぎも痛くてなかなか辛かったです💦
いつでもすぐに帰れるように、今夜は駿府城公園の内堀を走りました。結果、3周走って帰宅🏃‍♂️

熱海を後にして、渋滞にハマりながらも伊豆半島を南下。
pic2,3  竜宮窟に行ってきました😊無理やりな気もしますが、ハート型だそうです👍
pic4  竜宮窟をを下から見ると、こんな感じです😊
pic5  すぐ隣ではサンドスキーやっていました。
pic6〜8  帰りはループ橋へ。ただ走るんじゃなくて、下から橋を見上げたかったんです😆ようやく念願が叶いました😊なかなかの迫力で、大満足👍
pic9 ,10  で、旅の最中ストーリーにもあげていましたが、箱根関所で500円で購入したコレ、２日かけてようやくクリア😆十分に元は取れました👍

Arrivé en haut, j’étais mort ! 🥵 Mais pendant l’effort, j’ai cru voler. 🦅☺️

Aujourd’hui c’était sortie en mode pseudo-fractionné. J’ai commencé par aller chercher un KOM Strava qui me faisait de l’œil dans le village d’à côté : une côte à 10% de 280m bien connue des athlètes du coin. 📈

Les jambes étaient là, alors je me suis lancé comme une bombe. 💣 💥 Et à ma grande surprise, je suis arrivé en haut sans avoir l’impression de forcer. Comme si la côte était plus courte que d’habitude… Ça s’est fait tout seul. Sur mon petit nuage, ça a déroulé avec une fluidité jouissive. 🚀
J’ai parcouru le segment en 54’, soit 3’12”/km. Suffisamment pour obtenir la couronne. 👑 Youhou ! 🙌🏻 

J’avais repéré d’autres segments sur le chemin du retour, mais je me suis planté et suis parti trop tôt, ce qui m’a obligé à ralentir avant le fin, mon allure sur 1000m n’étant pas adaptée à du 1500m. 🤦🏻 J’ai fait un beau pop-corn !!! 🍿 😂 Ce sera pour la prochaine fois. 😜

Les compets’ me manquent, alors j’essaie de m’inventer des challenges. 💪🏻 Qui aurait cru que je deviendrais un chasseur de KOM… 😶
Vous vous fixez des objectifs quand vous courrez seuls, vous aussi ?

Bon pont à ceux qui le font ! 😍 Pour les autres, je vous envoie plein de courage ! 💌 😘

. 
Como todos los días son buenos para dar gracias, ya sea por estar aquí o por un acontecimiento extraordinario, hoy comparto con ustedes mis palabras de agradecimiento.
. 
Gracias, gracias, mil gracias.
.

.

※大学時代のマブ友達と最近めちゃ絡むんですが、走り以外の面で、普通にこなせる水準が高すぎて自分まだまだだなと感じました。負けてランねえ。

【出発】7:20
【就寝】22:50

▶︎つなぎ練習

LA DÉFENSE AU BASKET 

La partie offensive du basket est amusante mais la défense a beaucoup plus d’impact sur le succès de l’équipe. 

➪ Forcer le défenseur à prendre des tirs difficiles : 
 La chose la plus importante à retenir pour un joueur en matière de défense est de forcer le tir de son vis à vis. 
Il est important de se concentrer sur le processus consistant à faire déjouer l’attaque adverse et donc provoquer un tir à faible pourcentage. 

➪ Communiquer avec les coéquipiers : 
Tout au long de la séquence défensive, tes coéquipier doivent savoir où tu te trouves et ce qu’il se passe sur le terrain. 
Cela améliore la communication collective et peut entraîner une prise de confiance de certains joueurs.
« Il n’y a jamais eu de grande défense silencieuse » - Del Harris 

➪ Garde ton équilibre en toute circonstance : 
Le maintien de l’équilibre permet aux défenseurs de réagir rapidement aux mouvements et aux actions de l’attaquant. 
Un joueur offensif intelligent attaquera un défenseur déséquilibré et créera une situation de tir. 

🔺 Devenir un grand défenseur c’est aimer le défi

💥 FUNCTIONAL FRIDAY 💥 

Muscle Band Mobility Program. 

🤸🏽 EVERYONE should be including mobility work into their training to ensure they’re performing at their best and decreasing their risk of injury. 

😫 Without range of motion, your performance will suffer. 

💪🏼 Mobility exercises such as my Muscle Band Mobility Program is a great place to start prior to any workout. Mobilisation exercises increase your range of motion and stabilisation, or control of the muscles that surround each joint. Mobility incorporates flexibility and strength , it’s crucial to make you: 

🏋🏽‍♂️ SQUAT DEEPER 
🤸🏽‍♂️ PUSH HARDER, and 
🤾🏼‍♂️ JUMP HIGHER 

👩🏽‍💻 Because we spend so much time in poor static positions including in front of the TV, phone or computer our body gets tight and lacks both optimal range of motion and adequate activation of specific muscle groups. 

There are two main reasons to do mobility work prior to a workout: 

☝🏼 To prevent getting injured 
✌🏼 To get stronger 

The biggest priority for most is the latter but nothing will cease your gains like an impingement or strain that prevents you from lifting or training in the first place. 

Inadequate mobility and stability contribute to 90% of the injuries in a private practice. 

Having optimal mobility and movement allows you to achieve better positions which allow you to be more efficient in your lifts or movements which will translate to get stronger and faster. 

Do yourself a favour and add this in prior to your gym workouts or before trainings and games ⚽️🏀🎾🏉⚾️🏑🏏⛳️

banded donkey kicks 3x 12

banded side steps 3x 10 each way

kb sumo rdl to squat 3x 8
heels elevated goblet squat 3x 8

oh reverse lunge 3x 8 each leg 
oh air squat 3x 8

❗️Antrenman Bilgileri
👉🏻Antrenmandan önce 3-4 dk ısınıyoruz
👉🏻Her hareketi 30 sn yapıp 10 sn dinleniyoruz 
👉🏻Hareketleri bitirdikten sonra 1 dk  dinlenip tekrar hareketleri başa sarıyoruz 
👉🏻Toplam 5 set olacak şekilde tamamlıyoruz.Seviyene göre seti arttırabilirsiniz
👉🏻Antrenmanı ne çok aç ne de çok tok karnına yapıyoruz. 1 saat öncesine kadar yemek işini bitirmiş olmamız gerekiyor.

❗️Dikkat
👉🏻Yeni başladıysan set sayısını düşük tutabilirsin
👉🏻Tansiyon,kalp gibi kronik rahatsızlığı olanlar hareketleri yapmasınlar

🗣 “Você pode perguntar o que quiser que eu não vou responder”, alertou Koeman.

⚠️O presidente também quer saber o motivo de certas decisões táticas e da situação de certos jogadores, tanto os craques consagrados como outros que dificilmente tiveram um papel de liderança junto ao técnico holandês. 

⚠️Segundo fontes do clube, este encontro Laporta-Koeman não vai dar uma decisão sobre o futuro do treinador, que tem contrato em vigor até 2022. 

⚠️O presidente quer apenas ter informações de primeira mão e Laporta tem mostrado publicamente seu apoio ao trabalho de Koeman, algo que ele já fez na campanha eleitoral, sabendo que a figura do técnico holandês é especial na história do clube.

O Tênis é um esporte praticado entre dois oponentes ou duas duplas de oponentes em uma quadra dividida por uma rede, onde os jogadores usam raquetes para rebater uma pequena bola de um lado para o outro.
O jogo é iniciado com o saque de um dos jogadores. Devolvida a bola, ele continua até que um dos tenistas lance a bola na rede ou para fora da quadra. Marca-se o ponto aquele que conseguir fazer a bola tocar no solo de qualquer parte da quadra adversária.
O tênis possui uma pontuação que o subdivide em games/jogos e sets/partidas. Um game é um conjunto de pontos e um set é um conjunto de games.

Fala galera!! Depois de @masongreenwood e @skeptagram revelarem todos os detalhes da nova @nikefootball Phanton SK, a marca oficializou hoje o lançamento da chuteira e também deu todos os detalhes no que se referem a está colab fantástica!! .
Skepta é o primeiro artista musical a fazer uma parceria com a @nike em uma chuteira de alto desempenho. O design que serviu de inspiração para a criação da Phanton SK é uma borboleta vermelha, tomando como base a fase de metamorfose no qual o animal passa, já o solado e os swoosh’s cromados sao inspirados nas joias de prata que fazem parte do estilo do artista. .
A coleção não ficou restrita apenas a chuteira, também foi criado um Air Max que leva essas mesmas inspirações. .
Não é a primeira vez que as partes se unem para criar algo, mas a paixão de Skepta pelo futebol dessa vez falou mais alto e fez com que o projeto fosse criado e saísse do papel. .

🤙NIKE X SACAI VAPORWAFFLE SESAME🤙

La cultura japonesa ama las deportivas en los outfits de la calle. A millones de japoneses les encanta buscar los modelos más exclusivos y las mejores ediciones limitadas. Además, tienen muy buenos diseñadores urbanos, Nike lo sabe, y regularmente presenta colaboraciones con marcas japonesas. Sacai es una firma que fundó Chitose Abe hace 21 años y sus diseños disruptivos y modernos la han convertido en una marca de ropa urbana de lujo en todo el mundo. Las Nike x Sacai VaporWaffle sesame real son una combinación de las Pegasus de 1983 y las actuales Vaporfly.
 
El resultado de la fusión de estos dos modelos icónicos de Nike son estas nuevas Sacai. Un diseño con ADN runner, pero pensadas para ser las reinas de la calle. Fíjate en todos los detalles y la calidad de los materiales. ¡Muy top! Los colores están inspirados en la maratón que ganó Joan Benois Samuelson en 1984. Y la mayoría de los elementos están duplicados.

Highlights from last nights win

Хэй, guys ✌🏾
Чё там слышно по охр😉нительным кроссам?😍

А искусство то.. Не без намека.. 

В храме Конфуция, в городе Пинъяо на почётном месте стоят Ворота дракона. Легенда рассказывает, что однажды упорный и трудолюбивый карп шёл на нерест вверх по Жёлтой реке, перепрыгивая течение. Долог и труден был его путь, но он не оставлял выбранной дороги. Вдруг впереди возник водопад, с двух сторон окружённый горами. Это были Ворота Дракона. Карп перепрыгнул их, и неожиданно сам превратился в дракона, взмыв в небо. С тех пор, символическое преодоление таких ворот приносит необыкновенную удачу, крепкое здоровье здоровье и заслуженный успех. По-китайски эта знаменитая легенда называется  鲤鱼跳龙门 (lǐ yú tiào lóng mén) «Ли юй тяо лун мэнь». Поэтому китайцы любят дарить изображения прыгающего карпа, как пожелание всех видов благ. 

Так что не сворачивайте с выбранной дороги, каким бы тернистым и сложным не был пусть. И быть Вам драконами🐉🐲🐉🤟🏾

🐅 The Onitsuka Tiger Colorado 85 silhouette has been one of the most iconic for collaborations in the past, so we came up with something different, a trading card game that has been here for a long time, Yu-Gi-Oh!, this colourway is inspired by "a powerful engine of destruction, virtually invincible", the legendary Blue Eyes White Dragon.
This colourway has been designed directly from the SDK-E001 Blue Eyes White Dragon card in hand.
The upper features a cracked white/blue leather, blue flat grain leather overlays, the tiger stripes are made with a synthetic enamel finish so as the heel tab and a gradient colour on the rubber outsole.
On the removable insole you'll find the OG artwork printed with its ATK and DEF, as well as the level 8 stars.
There would be so many little details that you'd love on the paper tissue and box.

Tiger Stripes - Synthetic

News Flash - about 1/5 of the global cotton supply comes from Xinjiang China. Allegations that this cotton was produced through forced labour of Uyghurs has worried NGOs, brands, governments and consumers. 

International brands like H&M and Nike have called out against the malpractice and felt the retaliation of China, sending a clear message that brands have no right to get involved in government business. 

But on a political level the issue was used as well by the Trump administration, banning all US brands from sourcing Xinjiang cotton. The problem is that the textile supply chain lacks transparency and it is very difficult to trace the cotton from a t-shirt all the way back to the farm. On top of that cotton prices are skyrocketing all over the world.

RPE, HR, Pace, Power-All of the metrics used for running plans. 
.
The only metric I haven’t used personally-Power. So, looking forward to fall marathon training I thought it was timely to acquaint myself with this method. After some research and many recommendations I have chosen to purchase the Stryd foot pod/power meter.
.
Although I am not a fan of more technology-I do think as a Running Coach it’s important to understand all of the options available to my clients. There is no better way to do that than to commit and complete a @8020endurance training plan.
.

🏀 Top 500 NBA Greatest Players of All Time

#221 Lamar Odom [1999 - 2013]
📍SF / PF

961 Games - 13.3 PTS 8.4 REB 3.7 AST
🚨 PLAYOFFS - 108 Games - 13.0 PTS 8.8 REB 2.4 AST

🍾2x NBA Champ: Lakers - 2009 & 10
🔥1x 6th Man of the Year

🇫🇷 Odom est sélectionné par les Clippers en 4e position lors de la draft 1999. Il arrive dans une des plus mauvaises équipes de la NBA et devient tout de suite titulaire et un joueur très important du roster. Il réalise de bonnes saisons avec les Clippers mais son équipe ne parvient pas à jouer les Playoffs et Odom signe au Heat en 2003. Il est très performant lors de son année en Floride et aide la franchise de Miami à atteindre les Demi-finales de Conférence en 2004 (4-2 pour les Pacers). Cependant, il est envoyé quelques mois plus tard aux Lakers et s’intègre tout de suite au starting 5. Néanmoins, la franchise de Los Angeles est éliminée dès le 1er tour en 2006 et 2007 mais l’arrivée de Pau Gasol en 2008 permet à l’équipe de s’améliorer et de jouer les Finales NBA (4-2 pour les Celtics). Odom devient progressivement le 6e homme de l’équipe et il remporte le Championnat NBA en 2009 (4-1 face au Magic) et 2010 (4-3 face aux Celtics) aux côtés de Kobe Bryant. Son temps de jeu et ses statistiques diminuent lorsqu’il est envoyé aux Mavs en décembre 2011 puis aux Clippers en 2012 avec lesquelles il joue ses derniers matchs dans la ligue en 2013. 

🇺🇸 Odom was selected by the Clippers in 4th position during the 1999 draft. He joined one of the worst teams in the NBA and immediately became a starter and very important player on the roster. He played some good seasons with the Clippers but the team didn’t manage to play the POs. Odom signed to the Heat in 2003; he performed well in Florida and helped the Miami franchise reach the 2004 Conference Semifinals (4-2 to the Pacers). However, a few months later, he was sent to the Lakers and immediately integrated the starting 5. The Los Angeles franchise was eliminated in the 1st round in 2006 and 2007 but the arrival of Pau Gasol in 2008 allowed the team to progress and play the NBA Finals (4-2 to the Celtics). [cont’]

In this episode, I am wearing a pair of Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT in Black Monarch colorway. I initially thought that these were the continuation of Air Jordan 1 High Zoom line with full-length zoom air units exposed underneath the insoles that has been releasing since 2019. I soon discovered that Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT line was a completely new line of sneakers utilizing totally different cushioning setup. Instead of the exposed full-length zoom air, zoom bag is only imbedded in the heel area while the entire bottom is made out of a foam material encapsulated by rubber-trim outsole. Once again, I usually don’t wear my Jordans as soon as I pick them up because I have other 100 plus pairs in my collection waiting to be Un-DS-ed but this pair was different. These went straight to my feet early this year. To showcase how versatile this particular sneakers are for all ages, AJ1 High Zoom Air CMFT Black Monarch were put together with sable color long-sleeve t-shirt from Lululemon along with black dress pants from Giorgio Armani. Finally, overall style is further accentuated with a black sports jacket from Emporio Armani.

Zuerst wieder WarmUp und Mobilität 🥵 Wie gewohnt 6 Übungen insgesamt und natürlich je 2 Übungen im Supersatz mit 3 Sätzen pro Übung 👊🏼 Erster Supersatz Schulterdrücken mit der Langhantel und Facepulls mit Gummibändern, der zweite Supersatz Schulter und Nacken ziehen mit der SZ Stange und Frontheben mit der Kurzhantel, der dritte und letzte Supersatz war Nackenziehen mit der Langhantel und Seitheben mit den Kurzhanteln 💪🏼 Zum Cooldown, eine Stunde Laufband 🏃🏼 Wünsche Euch einen schönen Donnerstag Abend und bleibt gesund 🙏🏼

Today shoulder and neck training 💪🏼 First warm-up and mobility 🥵 As usual 6 exercises in total and of course 2 exercises in the superset with 3 sets per exercise 👊🏼 First superset of shoulder presses with the barbell and facepulls with elastic bands, the second superset of pulling shoulder and neck with the SZ bar and front raise with the dumbbell, the third and last superset was neck pulling with the barbell and lateral lifting with the dumbbells 💪🏼 To cool down, one hour treadmill 🏃🏼 Wish you a nice thursday evening and stay healthy 🙏🏼

-
TRY➡️SAVE ➡️SHARE

Today we have 2 body weight tabata circuits. Strapped for time? 🙄 each of these take less than 10 mins to complete.
-
The Prescription 🗒:
Tabata 1 - 
▪️8 rounds (4 sets of each exercise), 20 seconds work/10 seconds rest
▫️Switch between T1(A) and T1(B) on each working set.

Tabata 2 -
▪️9 rounds (3 sets of each exercise), 20 seconds work/10 seconds rest
▫️ Switch between T2(A), T2(B) and T2(C) on each working set.
-
The Keys 🔑:
Pace yourself. While the working sets may seem short, they add up! Don’t make the mistake of burning through the movements on the first set. Keep a steady pace so that your working sets don’t bleed into rest periods from burning out.

Thumbs up for a morning speed run!
.
Thanks to a genetic gift from my mama, my body likes to run fast. So speed days are my favorite days. 
.
Have you ever noticed how liberating, free, and unrestricted you feel when you run fast? Even if it’s for 20 seconds, I feel like the most powerful person on the planet. 
.
It’s not about the time on the watch, it’s the effort and freedom. The yin and the yang that is running.
.
Whether you had a long run, a speed run, or just thought about your next run, (or starting your first run!) I hope you find the power within that run that is yours.
.
Because each run, each say, gives us something. A lesson, power, health, and strength. ❤️ 🏃🏼‍♀️ 
.
.
.

A long-forgotten and rare Hip-Hop album by Kobe Bryant has been leaked 21 years after it was recorded back in the year 2000. The project, aptly titled ‘Kobe Bryant LP’, is considered a relic from the past, as only a few of its tracks had been published.

The full album was leaked, including 16 tracks with a runtime of 1 hour 1 minute. Kobe proves in the disc that he was a pretty capable rapper, and that Shaq wasn’t the only Laker who was able to drop some bars, but the most surprising aspect of the album is the amount of star power that Kobe got for the features. 

Nas, 50 Cent, Destiny’s Child were among the amazing featured artists, and even other solid artists from the time like Black Though and Beanie Sigel make an appearance. Supermodel Tyra Banks and battle rapped Broady Boy round out the guest list. 

Kobe’s sound is fascinating because he doesn’t really sound like an NBA player, or like Kobe Bryant, attempting to make gimmicky rap. Kobe had solid rhymes and schemes, and was ready to go rap in tough situations like street freestyle battles. The success of his NBA career is obvious, but maybe if he needed to rap to earn the bread, he wouldn’t have done half bad. 

At the end of the day, LL Cool J recommended Kobe to drop his rap ambitions and focus on his career. Obviously, that worked out in the end.
•Caught•

caption:
Wade or Harden All Time?
——
Im taking Dwade. Ive been seeing this debate recently and i wanna say a couple things about it. When Hardens career is over i do believe he will rank higher than Dwade. but in terms of resume and accolades at the age of 31, Wade had 3 chips, 1 finals MVP and a scoring title by the age of 31. and Harden has only 1 MVP and 3 scoring titles. granted, wade did have shaq and bron but the thing is when he won finals mvp in 2006, he was only 24 in his 3rd year in the league. That’s insanely impressive imo. I feel like harden has more to prove if he wants to be considered above Wade. But by no means am i slandering harden that man can play basketball. and ill say it one more time, by then end of his career he will be ranked above wade i just don’t believe he is right now.

Doppelsieg beim Hawaii Halbmarathon🥇🥇

Von Anfang April bis Anfang Mai hatte ich einen Monat lang Zeit den virtuellen Hawaii Halbmarathon zu laufen. Angeboten wurden 5 km, 10 km und Halbmarathon. Da der Zeitraum lang genug war, war mir klar, dass ich über alle Distanzen an den Start gehen möchte. Zuerst startete ich beim Halbmarathon, den ich im Stadion absolvierte und in 1:16:02 Stunden meine offizielle Bestzeit unterbieten konnte. Eine Woche später folgten die 10 km in 35:20 Minuten und zum Abschluss konnte ich 5 km in 16:44 Minuten laufen. Damit landete ich beim 10er auf Rang zwei, die anderen beiden Distanzen konnte ich gewinnen, worüber ich mich sehr gefreut habe.📸 @sophiasperception

💡 10 Facts about Ronaldinho that you don't know.

Fact 1.
▶ His main playing position is as an attacking midfielder or forward.

Fact 2.
▶ He won the FIFA world player of the year award in 2004 and 2005.

Fact 3.
▶ He became a Spanish citizen in January 2007.

Fact 4.
▶ He was named to the FIFA 100, a list of the greatest footballers compiled by fellow countryman Pele and to the FIFPro world consecutively from 2004 to 2007.

Fact 5.
▶ Ronaldinho has played 97 matches and scored 33 goals for the Brazil national football team.

Fact 6.
▶ He was an integral part of the 2002 FIFA world cup winning team starring alongside Ronaldo and Rivaldo in an attacking trio and was named in the FIFA world cup All-star team.

Fact 7.
▶ Renowned for his outrageous skill, trick, dribbling, overhead kicks, blind passes and free kicks. Ronaldinho is widely regarded to be one of the best footballers of his generation.

Fact 8.
▶ Ronaldinho's 2005 Nike advertisement went viral on YouTube becoming the site's first video to reach one million views.

Fact 9.
▶ Ronaldinho joined forces with the United Nations to educate the public about AIDS in 2011 and on June 2013 he launched his own line of condoms named Sex Free.

Fact 10.
▶ His football skills began to blossom at the age of 8, and he was first given the nickname RONALDINHO because he was often youngest and the smallest player in youth club matches.

Adidas D Rose 11 „Born to do this“ 2021 👶🏻 🏀 
Danke @hombre4life für deine Empfehlung!

Eckdaten ⬇️
Gewicht: 420-430g
Dämpfung: Lightstrike
Fit: Halbe Nummer kleiner nehmen!
Preis: 150,00€
Gekauft bei: Adidas
Verfügbarkeit: 🟢

Bewertung 🔍
Traction: A-
Dämpfung: B
Lockdown: B-
Gewicht: C+
Materialien: B-

Der 11te Signature Schuh des jüngsten MVP aller Zeiten trägt den schillernden Namen „born to do this“.
Wer erinnert sich nicht gerne an den explosiven D Rose 2008-2011 der uns so viele schöne Momente beschert hat?
Umso schöner, dass D Rose jetzt seinen zweiten Frühling bei den Knicks erlebt und richtig gut performed. 
Die Traction erinnert sehr an den D Rose 7, welcher definitiv die besten Traction seiner Schuh-Linie hatte und der 11er kann da auf jeden Fall mithalten. Eine Empfehlung für Indoor und Outdoor!
Für die Dämpfung benutzt Adidas die Lightstrike Technologie, die mir sehr gut gefällt, fast so komfortabel wie das allseits bekannte Boost aber deutlich leichter und reaktions-freudiger. Speziell im hinteren Bereich des Fußes ist die Dämpfung eine Wohltat, vorne sieht’s etwas mau aus.
Der Lockdown und Support ist gut wenn man die Schnürsenkel noch höher schnürt, den nur dann hat man das Gefühl fest im Schuh zu sitzen. 
Das Material ist okay, erfüllt seinen Job, ist lightweight aber keineswegs Premium wie zb bei einem Lebron Schuh.
Zum Fit lässt sich sagen, dass der Schuh wie fast jeder Adidas größer ausfällt und man eine halbe Nummer kleiner nehmen sollte.
Ich bin zufrieden mit dem D Rose 11 - einer der wenigen Adidas Schuhe die ich bisher getestet hab und die ich weiterhin tragen würde. 

Was haltet ihr von der D Rose Linie? Welchen fandet ihr bisher am Besten?

Welchen Schuh soll ich als nächstes reviewen ❓
Schreibt mir einen Kommentar und innerhalb von 7 Tagen (falls der Schuh verfügbar ist) kriegt ihr ein Review! 🏀🤝

#throwbackthursday to my 2016 NPC USA prep for Classic Physique. 

I was shopping for this speedo for a photo shoot with @billcomstock. The trunks at the time were the box style and I preferred these as they look more like the trunks worn in the 70’s and early 80’s. I’m glad they’ve since changed to this style. 

They are Nike but we actually took a sharpie to the logo for the shoot to make them look like plain black trunks. lol The shoot went well and I got a lot of great pics at Gold’s Venice from this. 

I liked this look better than the one that I ultimately brought to stage. I was still too heavy for the division here, but I liked the fullness. I’d get leaner by show time to make weight but would loose some roundness to the muscle in the process. They’ve since increased the weight cap so I’m looking forward to what V2.0 will look like this next go round. 💪🏼
